{{coor title d|54.4803|N|37.6975|E}}

[[Image:Coat of Arms of Yasnogorsk (Tula oblast) (1987).png|thumb|120px|Coat of arms of Yasnogorsk]]

'''Yasnogorsk''' ({{lang-ru|<U+042F><U+0441><U+043D><U+043E><U+0433><U+043E>&#769;<U+0440><U+0441><U+043A>}}) is a [[types of settlements in Russia|town]] in [[Tula Oblast]], [[Russia]], located on the [[Vashana River]] ([[Oka River|Oka]]'s [[tributary]]), 35&nbsp;km north of [[Tula, Russia|Tula]].  Population: 18,588 ([[Russian Census (2002)|2002 Census]]); 21,292 ([[Soviet Census (1989)|1989 Census]]).

The village of '''Laptevo''' ({{lang|ru|<U+041B><U+0430>&#769;<U+043F><U+0442><U+0435><U+0432><U+043E>}}) has been known since the 15th&ndash;16th centuries.   It received town status and renamed '''Laptev''' ({{lang|ru|<U+041B><U+0430>&#769;<U+043F><U+0442><U+0435><U+0432>}}) in 1958.  It was renamed Yasnogorsk in 1965.

